{
  "stem": "232.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, we came to this camp Agde, and it turned out to be a rotten place.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, there were barracks, empty barracks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We came there with children, women, and families-- you know, whole families-- and once they put us in, there was a gate with-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] what do you call this-- barbed wire, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] empty barracks.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were some soldiers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They came, OK, you get ready, get some straw and make your-- make your beds to, to sleep for tonight.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the, the men and the boys-- like me, I went out with the, the men to get-- there was a whole mountain like of straw, straw bundled, you know, for-- like on the fields.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We took this.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We took it in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They gave us like a sack.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We filled the sack with straw, and this was our mattress.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the white sheets were our shirts.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, they were just trying to tell us that we shouldn't revolt or something to get us into this camp.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So once we were in there, we had to do the best we could.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The, the women and children prepared, prepared the, the, the straw bags for the night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when, when the straw mattress were finished, the authorities-- this was a camp with-- there were soldiers already, and police, gendarmerie.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They came into the barracks, says OK.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "All the men line up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They took out the men, and they put them in another camp-- I mean, in a different area of barracks, separated also by barbed wire, where women and men could not see each other.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was in the middle.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I could stay with my mother, or I could go with my dad.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I stayed with my mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
